</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="278" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,866,1287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1226,1251]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from the Atlantic and the Indo-Pacific; previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1219,1314,1226,1251]" name="Réunion" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Réunion</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Guille" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" refString="Guille, A. &amp; Ribes, S. (1981) Echinodermes associes aux Scleractiniaires d'un recif frangeant de l'ile de La Reunion (ocean Indien). Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire Naturelle, 3, 1, 73 - 92." type="journal article" year="1981">
Guille &amp; Ribes 
<number box="[221,280,1263,1287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Stohr" box="[293,480,1262,1287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" refString="Stohr, S., Conand, C. &amp; Boissin, E. (2008) Brittle stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from La Reunion and the systematic position of Ophiocanops Koehler, 1922. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 153, 545 - 560. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2008.00401. x" type="journal article" year="2008">
Stöhr 
<emphasis box="[359,416,1262,1286]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[422,480,1263,1287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and Rodrigues (
<bibRefCitation author="Rowe" box="[672,959,1262,1287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" refString="Rowe, F. W. E. &amp; Richmond, M. D. (2004) A preliminary account of the shallow-water echinoderms of Rodrigues, Mauritius, western Indian Ocean. Journal of Natural History, 3273 - 3314. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 002229301695105" type="book chapter" year="2004">
Rowe &amp; Richmond 
<number box="[898,959,1263,1287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
