<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="278" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1477,1790]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1513,1538]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Remarks.</emphasis>
A five-armed species, much bigger (DD: 
<quantity box="[789,856,1514,1538]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
) than 
<taxonomicName box="[925,1053,1514,1537]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiactidae" genus="Ophiactis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="savignyi">
<emphasis box="[925,1053,1514,1537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
<collectingCountry box="[925,948,1514,1537]" name="Iceland" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">O</collectingCountry>
. savignyi
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(max DD in 
<collectingCountry box="[1203,1298,1513,1538]" name="Réunion" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Reunion</collectingCountry>
island: 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.62" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" unit="mm" value="2.62">2.62 mm</quantity>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Stohr" box="[210,404,1549,1574]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" refString="Stohr, S., Conand, C. &amp; Boissin, E. (2008) Brittle stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from La Reunion and the systematic position of Ophiocanops Koehler, 1922. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 153, 545 - 560. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2008.00401. x" type="journal article" year="2008">
Stöhr 
<emphasis box="[279,337,1549,1573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[346,404,1550,1574]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), with two distal oral papillae and six arm spines along the length of the arm. The overall colouration is pale brown. Among the 
<number box="[597,624,1586,1610]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="11.0">11</number>
shallow IWP 
<taxonomicName box="[790,899,1585,1609]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiactidae" genus="Ophiactis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[790,899,1585,1609]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Ophiactis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, only four have two oral papillae. The colouration, size of the adoral shields and length of the arms (~ 
<number box="[904,918,1621,1646]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="6.0">6</number>
DD), of our specimen are consistent with 
<taxonomicName class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiactidae" genus="Ophiactis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="picteti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
<collectingCountry box="[1409,1432,1622,1645]" name="Iceland" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">O</collectingCountry>
. picteti
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen was found in a crevice of the fire coral 
<emphasis box="[837,1090,1657,1681]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
<taxonomicName box="[837,1086,1657,1681]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Milleporidae" genus="Millepora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="platyphylla">Millepora platyphylla</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Abundance: 
<number box="[1238,1253,1658,1682]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1.0">1</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="278" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1477,1790]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1693,1718]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Distribution.</emphasis>
Described from the Amboina (
<collectingCountry box="[726,839,1693,1718]" name="Indonesia" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Moluccas</collectingCountry>
, de 
<bibRefCitation author="Loriol" box="[893,1049,1693,1718]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" refString="De Loriol, P. (1893 b) Echinodermes de la Baie d'Amboine. Revue Suisse zoologique, 1, 359 - 426, pls 13 - 15." type="journal article" year="1893" yearSuffix="b">
Loriol 
<number box="[975,1034,1693,1718]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1893.0">1893</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
), it has also been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,299,1729,1754]" name="Mozambique" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Balinsky" box="[313,481,1729,1754]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" refString="Balinsky, J. B. (1957) The Ophiuroidea of Inhaca Island. Annals of the Natal Museum, 14, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="1957">
Balinsky 
<number box="[421,481,1729,1754]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1957.0">1957</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); Aldabra (
<bibRefCitation author="Sloan" box="[606,797,1729,1754]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" refString="Sloan, N. A., Clark, A. M. &amp; Taylor, J. D. (1979) The echinoderms of Aldabra and their habitats. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Zoology, 37 (2), 81 - 128." type="journal article" year="1979">
Sloan 
<emphasis box="[677,733,1729,1753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[740,797,1730,1754]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1979.0">1979</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[859,994,1729,1754]" name="Madagascar" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cherbonnier" box="[1009,1323,1729,1754]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" refString="Cherbonnier, G. &amp; Guille, A. (1978) Echinodermes: Ophiurides. In: Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle (Eds.), Faune de Madagascar. Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique, Paris, pp. 1 - 272." type="book chapter" year="1978">
Cherbonnier &amp; Guille 
<number box="[1263,1323,1730,1754]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1978.0">1978</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This is a first record for 
<collectingCountry box="[321,416,1765,1790]" name="Réunion" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Réunion</collectingCountry>
and the Mascarene Islands.
</paragraph>
